# Role Boundaries

## The Golden Rule

**Do your job. Don't do someone else's job.**

If you find a bug outside your domain, document it and hand it off. Do not fix it yourself.

## Agent 01 (PM) — DOES NOT WRITE CODE

The PM plans, delegates, tracks, and communicates. The PM never implements features or fixes bugs unless the human explicitly overrides this rule. If PM notices an issue, they file a bug ticket and assign it to the owning agent.

## File Ownership (who changes what)

| Files / Area | Primary Owner | Consult |
|---|---|---|
| `game/engine.py` | Agent 03 | Agent 08 (UI hooks) |
| `game/entities/` | Agent 05 | Agent 03 (contracts) |
| `game/systems/combat.py`, `economy.py` | Agent 05 | Agent 06 (AI hooks) |
| `game/systems/bounty.py` | Agent 05 | Agent 06 |
| `game/systems/spawner.py`, `lairs.py` | Agent 05 | Agent 07 (scenarios) |
| `ai/basic_ai.py`, `ai/providers/` | Agent 06 | Agent 03 (determinism) |
| `game/ui/` | Agent 08 | Agent 03 (input routing) |
| `game/graphics/` | Agent 09 | Agent 08 (UI icons) |
| `game/audio/` | Agent 14 | Agent 03 (event contract) |
| `game/sim/` | Agent 03 | Agent 04 (determinism) |
| `tools/` | Agent 12 | Agent 11 (QA tools) |
| `config.py` | Shared | PM awareness required |
| `assets/` | Agent 09 (sprites), Agent 14 (audio) | Agent 12 (validator) |

## Cross-Domain Changes

If your task requires editing a file you don't own:
1. Check if the owner has recent changes that might conflict
2. Make the minimal change needed
3. Document it in your agent log
4. Note it for the file owner so they can review

## What "Consult" Means

- You may be asked to review or advise on changes in that area
- You don't implement unless the owner delegates to you
- If you see a problem, tell the owner — don't fix it silently
